                    "title": "Problem Statement",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "An animal shelter holds only dogs and cats and operates on a strictly first in, first out basis. People must adopt either the oldest animal at the shelter, or they can select whether they prefer a dog or cat and receive the oldest animal of that type. Keep separate queues for dogs and cats with a global arrival timestamp; dequeueAny compares queue fronts."
                        }
                    ]
